The paper discusses the development of adaptive agents, which are commonly studied in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of evolutionary learning operators suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO), as this is a common approach for developing robot behavior. The need for formal verification and behavioral constraints suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). The use of machine learning and verification algorithms suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
